    "personality": {
      "traits": [
        "She is **meticulous** in both her attire and her complex plans, valuing dark, cold elegance above all else.",
        "**Introspective** and initially **socially uncomfortable** (prior to her vampirism), she relies on calculated charm now.",
        "**Obsessively driven** by the quest for perfection and the ultimate form of unbreaking undeath.",
        "**Cautious and patient**, she is always willing to play the long political and magical game to achieve her ends."
      ],
      "ideals": [
        "**Perfection:** True mastery lies in engineering a form of undeath that surpasses the limitations of life and standard vampirism.",
        "**Control:** The only true freedom is found in absolute control over one's own fate and the fate of others."
      ],
      "bonds": [
        "Her former life as an Amnian sage must never be publicly known; it is a point of shame.",
        "Her most prized work, the **Bloodforged Ascension** research, is the only thing she values more than her own life.",
        "The **Steel Defender** is her original masterpiece and closest, if subservient, companion."
      ],
      "flaws": [
        "She views most living creatures as simply **components**‚Äîeither for her experiments or for feeding.",
        "Her **obsessive need for perfection** can make her rigid and resistant to changing a flawless plan, even when circumstances change.",
        "She harbors a deep, secret **fear of the divine** (hence the fear of divine wrath weakness)."
      ]
    },
    "motivations": [
      "Achieve 'The Bloodforged Ascension'‚Äîa final, self-engineered form of undeath immune to all traditional vampire weaknesses (sunlight, running water, stake, etc.).",
      "Expand her influence within Amn and the surrounding regions, creating a society where her kind can exist without fear."
    ],
    "tactics": "Lady Erliza fights with a calculated, cold fury. She prioritizes **Control and Battlefield Manipulation**, using her high AC and immunities to draw enemy attention while her Steel Defender and charmed minions flank. She uses **Flash of Genius** defensively, saving her party from key effects, and uses the **Bloodforged Sunlight Shield** tiara's reaction to negate radiant damage or critical lines of sight. She opens combat with area control spells like *Wall of Force* or *Resilient Sphere* from her stored spells and scrolls to divide the party. For offense, she relies on her **Multiattack** (Claw/Bite) combined with **Arcane Jolt** for burst damage and healing, saving her spell slots for utility and devastating high-level scrolls like *Forcecage* or *Disintegrate*.",
    "hooks": [
      "Lady Erliza is funding an underground network of arcane-mechanical workshops that are secretly kidnapping high-Con human males for a mysterious, blood-based 'experiment' (her ascendance research).",
      "A key artifact or formula needed by the party is known to be in her possession, hidden within Snowdown Keep.",
      "One of the party's former mentors or family members was once a colleague of Erliza's and is now either her unwilling servant (charmed) or a failed subject of her Bloodforged Ascension."
    ],
    "notes": [
      "The mixture of Artificer infusions and magic items (total 16 attunements) is a deliberate homebrew rule in this setting to reflect Erliza's unique nature and power.",
      "The spell list includes both Artificer and Wizard spells, justifying the Wizard feats.",
      "Spell Save DC and Attack Bonus are calculated using INT 20 (base 5) + Proficiency Bonus 7 + Bloodforged All-purpose Tool (Infusion +3) = 15 Attack / 23 DC.",
